 close calls. Well dig in just after the jump.</p><h3>How we scored the games</h3><p>Just to recap, each game was run on three fronts. First, we counted up the polls for each game. Secondly, we counted up votes on Twitter. Finally, we counted up comments generated (if they were) on the competitors blogs. Top score won.</p><p><span id="more-17441"></span></p><h3>Results of The Theme Foundry vs. ThemeFuse</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>15. ThemeFuse: 77</span></li><li><span>2. The Theme Foundry: 49</span></li></ul><p>Winner: ThemeFuse, who will be competing again on <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">April 21</a>.</p><h3>Results ofTokokoo vs. Standard Theme</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>10. Standard Theme: 141</span></li><li><span>7. Tokokoo: 41</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Standard Theme, who will be competing again on<a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">April 21</a>.</p><h3>Results ofDIYThemes vs. ThemeForce</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>15. ThemeForce: 42</span></li><li><span>2. DIYThemes: 62</span></li></ul><p>Winner: DIYThemes, who will be competing again on<a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">April 21</a>.</p><h3>Results ofGorilla Themes vs. WPShower</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>10. WPShower: 34</span></li><li><span>7. Gorilla Themes: 44</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Gorilla Themes, who will be competing again on<a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">April 21</a>.</p><h3>Results ofPagelines vs. Wonder Themes</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>15. Wonder Themes: 85</span></li><li><span>2. Pagelines: 61</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Wonder Themes, who will be competing again on<a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">April 21</a>.</p><h3>Results ofWPZoom vs. Viva Themes</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>10. Viva Themes: 21</span></li><li><span>7. WPZoom: 125</span></li></ul><p>Winner: WPZoom, who will be competing again on<a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">April 21</a>.</p><h3>Results ofiThemes vs. ThemeWarrior</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>15. ThemeWarrior: 40</span></li><li><span>2. iThemes: 72</span></li></ul><p>Winner: iThemes, who will be competing again on<a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">April 21</a>.</p><h3>Results ofDev4Press vs. Indonez</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>10. Indonez: 44</span></li><li><span>7. Dev4Press: 57</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Dev4Press, who will be competing again on<a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">April 21</a>.</p><h3>What do you think of the results so far?</h3><p>Were beginning to see results show up on the big<a title="Theme Madness 2011 Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">Theme Madness Bracket</a>. How do you think the results are shaking out? Are you surprised by any of the results so far? How are your own personal brackets going?</p><h3>Updated Theme Madness Schedule</h3><table id="wp-table-reloaded-id-14-no-1" class="wp-table-reloaded wp-table-reloaded-id-14"><thead><tr class="row-1 odd">